title: Estimated non-point source (NPS) ungaged loads — anlz_nps_ungaged
text: function estimates pollutant loads non-point sources ungaged (unmonitored) basins within Tampa Bay watershed. approach combines spatial land use data, rainfall patterns, hydrologic modeling, empirical relationships estimate monthly nutrient sediment loads.  Several steps followed: Data Preparation: Processes land use data logistic regression modeling calculates inverse distance-weighted rainfall data sub-basin. Flow Estimation: Uses logistic regression model predict monthly streamflow ungaged basins based : Current month rainfall 2-month lagged rainfall Land use percentages (urban, agriculture, wetlands, forest) Seasonal patterns (wet season: July-October, dry season: November-June) Urban development intensity (Group : <19% urban, Group B: ≥19% urban) Hydrologic soil group characteristics Runoff Coefficient Application: Applies land use soil-specific runoff coefficients distribute predicted flows across different landscape types within basin. Load Calculation: Estimates pollutant loads using Event Mean Concentrations (EMCs) different land use categories (CLUCSID), calculating: Total Nitrogen (TN) loads Total Phosphorus (TP) loads Total Suspended Solids (TSS) loads Biochemical Oxygen Demand (BOD) loads Stormwater-specific loads (different EMCs certain categories) Spatial Framework: analysis uses nested spatial hierarchy: Bay Segments: Major subdivisions Tampa Bay (1-7, 55 Lower Boca Ciega Bay) Basins: Hydrologic sub-basins, including USGS gaged ungaged areas Land Use Polygons: Detailed spatial units combining jurisdiction, land use (FLUCCS codes), soil characteristics Flow Prediction Models: function uses season- development-specific regression equations: Separate models wet vs. dry seasons Separate models low-development (Group ) vs. high-development (Group B) areas Models account antecedent moisture conditions lagged rainfall terms Load Estimation: Pollutant loads calculated : Load = Flow × EMC × Unit Conversions EMCs vary land use category (CLUCSID).  Special handling applied water bodies certain wetland types (CLUCSIDs 18, 20), assigned zero stormwater loads. Requires following inputs: tbbase: data frame containing polygon areas combined data layer bay segment, basin, jurisdiction, land use data, soils, Stored tbbase created (takes hour ) util_nps_tbbase. rain: data frame rainfall data. See util_nps_getextflow. bellshlpth: character, path file containing Bell shoals data. See util_nps_getextflow.
